summary: This is an email chain from August 2020 regarding an annual evidence inventory for the NYPD FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force. It confirms the status of several evidence items (laptops and other items) under specific case numbers, noting some are with an SA, some are with the sender, some were returned to NYPD property, and some are at CART.

persons.name: Offie Services Supervisor
persons.context: Sent the initial email on August 11, 2020, requesting confirmation for an annual evidence inventory.

events.title: Annual Evidence Inventory
events.description: The NYPD FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force is conducting its annual evidence inventory.

locations: New York Field Office Federal Bureau of Investigation
keyFacts: Evidence items related to case numbers 305D-NY-2944995, 50D-NY-3027571, 50D-NY-3067659, and 50D-NY-3077720 are being tracked.
A laptop (item 305D-NY-2944995 1B2) is in the possession of an FBI Special Agent (SA) for review.
Some evidence items (from 50D-NY-3067659) were returned to the NYPD Bronx property clerk for return to owner.
Other items (from 50D-NY-3077720) remain at CART (Computer Analysis and Response Team).
The communication is from the NYPD FBI Child Exploitation Human Trafficking Task Force, indicating ongoing investigative activity in 2020.
